output_data.summary: Follow-up psychiatric visit focused on assessing response to a 4-week trial of *Sertraline* 50mg amid escalating symptoms of a *Major Depressive Episode*.
output_data.reasoning: The patient reports severe depressive symptoms including early morning awakening, psychomotor slowing, and passive death ideation. Safety screening ruled out active intent. The session focused on medication adjustment (increasing *Sertraline* to 100mg) and brief behavioral interventions.
